To address the security issue of having a hardcoded password in the application.yml file, you can externalize the password to a separate configuration file. You can store the password securely in a separate properties file and then reference it in the application.yml file.

1. Create a separate properties file to store the password. For example, create a file named `cassandra.properties` and store the password in it:
   ```
   cassandra.password=En3kN#gh
   ```

2. Update the application.yml file to reference the password from the external properties file:
   ```
   spring:
     application:
       name: $(SPRING_APPLICATION_NAME: audit-engine)
     profiles:
       active: development
     logging:
       level:
         root: info
         org.springframework.web: info
         org.hibernate: info
     collection:
       orchestrator:
         dbpoll:
           interval: 5000
     async:
       core:
         pool:
           size: 5
     main:
       allow-bean-definition-overriding: true
     config:
       activate:
         on-profile: development
     cassandra:
       request:
         timeout: 20000
       keyspace-name: enmv_custominterfaces
       contact-points: 10.136.209.121, 10.136.209.93, 10.136.209.124, 10.136.209.122
       port: 9042
       username: enmv_cusintf_usr
       password: ${cassandra.password}
       local-datacenter: cospj
       connection:
         pool:
           local:
             size: 4
           remote:
             size: 4
             connect-timeout: 20000
     kafka:
       init-query-timeout: 20s
       bootstrap-servers: localhost:9092
       producer:
         topic-name: 3459-DEV-COLLECTION-REQUEST-QUEUE
         key-serializer: org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer
         value-serializer: org.springframework.kafka.support.serializer.JsonSerializer
     json:
       trusted:
         packages: org.vdsi.space.collections.Entities
       add:
         type: false
     server:
       port: 8080
   ```

By using `${cassandra.password}` in the application.yml file, the password will be resolved from the external properties file `cassandra.properties`.

Now, the password is externalized and stored securely in the separate configuration file.